## Plan

**Approach:** Premise-checked the 4 audit sub-items. INCLUDE 2/3/4 (clean, zero-behavior-change internal cli refactors). DROP sub-item 1 (inferMediaType move) as a layering regression, not an improvement. Bundle stays ONE commit (all changes confined to internal/cli, no package moves, no exported API).

**Sub-item decisions:**
- (1) inferMediaType -> artifactstore: DROP. artifactstore.AddContent(role,mediaType,content) is content-only / path-agnostic (store.go:66 never touches paths; caller supplies mediaType). inferMediaType maps a file EXTENSION->media-type, a filesystem/IO concern; all 3 callers (capture.go:257, capture.go:552, capture_run.go:381) are CLI code reading files. Moving a path->mediatype table into a content-addressed byte store inverts layering and would force an exported artifactstore.InferMediaType for a cli-only helper. It already lives in the right layer. The audit was wrong.
- (2) Dedup retro subject extraction: INCLUDE. retroSubjectsList (retro.go:257-289, type indexed) and the inline block in printRetroDetail (retro.go:309-335, type indexedSubject) are byte-identical sort-by-(prefix,index) over subject_run.N/bead.N; differ only in type name + final step (join vs print).
- (3) Collapse validateRunIDExtra (run.go:134) + validateRetroIDExtra (retro.go:235): INCLUDE, keeping the validator distinction. They call DIFFERENT validators in different packages (runmanifest.IsValidRunID vs retro.IsValidRetroID), so the shared helper takes the pre-computed validity bool + kind.
- (4) formatHarness helper: INCLUDE. The 3 sites (run.go:167-172 stage, run.go:225-230 seat, retro.go:370-375 producer) share the exact 'name' vs 'name version' decision; only prefix/indent/context differs. A pure formatHarness(Harness) string (returning the joined inner value, NOT printing) is cleanly reusable at all 3.

